      <h2>My Second JavaScript Example</h2>

      <h3>What Can JavaScript Do?</h3>

      <p>JavaScript can change HTML attribute values.</p>

      <p>In this case JavaScript changes the value of the src (source) attribute of an image.</p>

      <button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='images/pic_bulbon.gif'">Turn on the light</button>

      <img id="myImage" src="images/pic_bulboff.gif" style="width:100px">

      <button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='images/pic_bulboff.gif'">Turn off the light</button>


      <p id="demoFontSize">JavaScript can change the style of an HTML style element fontSize.</p>

      <button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demoFontSize').style.fontSize='35px'">Click to make me BIGGER!</button>

      <button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demoFontSize').style.fontSize='15px'">Click to make me smaller!</button>

      <p id="demo">JavaScript can hide HTML elements.</p>

      <button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo').style.display='none'">Click Me!</button>

      <button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('demo').style.display='list-item'">Click Me!</button>


      <p id="scriptdemo">Ron Was Here.</p>

      <script>
        document.getElementById("scriptdemo").innerHTML = "I changed wahat was here from a script tag.  :-)";
